title: Asian Bench Press Championship: Fahad claims gold; Salim takes bronze
text:
Follow us on Asian Bench Press Championship: Fahad claims gold; Salim takes bronze L-R: Salim al Auladthani, Ahmed al Hasani and Fahad al Nadabi celebrate their podium finishes on Sunday Muscat Daily staff writer October 05, 2015 
Fahad al Nadabi earned Oman's fourth gold medal on Sunday when he won the sub-junior -105kg category title in the ongoing Asian Bench Press Championship at the Sultan Qaboos Sports Complex. 
The youngster lifted a total of 150kg to claim the top honours and boost the host nation's tally of gold medals. 
Oman had won three gold medals on Friday and Saturday, and national coach Ahmed al Hasani was confident of another successful day. 
“The Omani sub-junior and junior lifters are quite strong and have been training hard over the past many months for this championship. Fahad is a talented lifter and I am happy that he claimed the gold today,” said Hasani. 
The host nation added one more bronze on Sunday when Salim al Auladthani won the third place in the -93kg junior category. 
With just a day to go for the conclusion of Oman's campaign at the championship, the hosts' medals tally has risen to 11, including four gold, three silver and four bronze. 
With the national coach expecting a few more medals on Monday, the 18-member team's performance has been 'satisfying' in Hasani's words. 
“Four of the five sub-junior team lifters have fetched medals so far and three of the six from the junior team have been on the podium. It is encouraging to see the young lifters do so well and it augurs well for the future of powerlifting in the country,” said Hasani. Similar content
